AGI - "Thursday, May 9, the hearings will be held in the Committee of Inquiry on the disappearance of Emanuela&nbsp; Orlandi&nbsp; and Mirella Gregori", announces the deputy of the League Riccardo Augusto Marchetti, Vice-President of the Commission itself. "We will start - anticipate - with the family of the two young people and listen to among the first Pietro&nbsp;Orlandi, brother of Emanuela, who in these years with courage never stopped looking for the truth, and that I thank for being immediately available." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"The hope is to find useful elements that can guide us towards concrete and definitive answers that the families of the two young people disappeared and the whole country have been waiting for for over forty years," says Marchetti. "I strongly wanted this Committee of Inquiry to be constituted - the exponent of the Leghist - because it was necessary that Parliament also make its contribution. We will carry out this commitment with seriousness to shed light on events still covered by too many questions: our goal is truth and we will pursue it with determination."
