AGI - The Codacons against Vannacci. The Association of Consumers presented an exposition to 104 Procure of the Republic, throughout Italy, the
<span>n with regard to the General's declarations on school with disabilities, asking the judiciary to open an investigation in the light of possible penally relevant cases such as that of "Propaganda and instigation to delinquere> for reasons of ethnic and religious racial discrimination". </span
&nbsp;
"We do not want to enter into the merits of the general's political choices, and in this place we do not contest its candidacy in the next European elections >nei we intend to interfere with the preferences of the Italians vote - clarifies the Codacons - However some statements attributed to Vannacci, for their severity and danger, impose an intervention of the judiciary > aimed at ascertaining whether the same can constitute a crime as provided for by our order.
&nbsp;
“In particular, the phrase on separate classes for disabled people is alarmed,” writes the Codacons in the expos – It would seem that, according to the General, the disabled should be separated from the most fortunate students of them, and even separate classes should be formed so as to allow the valorization of the capacities of each. The statement in question is contrary to the provisions of Law 517/77 > which clearly proposes tools and purposes for the integration of pupils with disabilities. Such a reasoning appears discriminatory and would seem to all intents and purposes a propaganda of ideas based on superiority. As well known conduct of this type can be suitable for integrating the crime provided for by art. 604 bis c.p., entitled “Propaganda and incitement to delinquer for reasons of ethnic and religious racial discrimination”.
&nbsp;
The Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disability lays down the basic requirements for the rights of persons with disabilities and has a legally binding character. Its purpose is to promote, protect and guarantee the full and equal enjoyment of all human rights and all fundamental freedoms by persons with disabilities, and promote respect for their intrinsic dignity."
&nbsp;
The Codacons therefore asked 104 Procures of all Italy to prepare the necessary controls to ascertain first of all the answer to the reality of the facts reported by the media and the conduct of the necessary and rigorous investigations and verifications in order to ascertain the possibility of configuring of cases such as the crime provided for by article 604 bis c.p. and every criminal case that is identified.

